  "accepted_examples": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_ms": 0,
      "end_ms": 9166,
      "duration_ms": 9166,
      "text": "The Bhagavadg\u012bt\u0101 told by K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a to Arjuna was not named by K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a Himself.",
      "duration_seconds": 9.166,
      "duration_bucket": "8_20s"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_ms": 9166,
      "end_ms": 16566,
      "duration_ms": 7400,
      "text": "This name was given by Sage Vy\u0101sa, who was the devotee of God.",
      "duration_seconds": 7.4,
      "duration_bucket": "5_8s"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_ms": 16566,
      "end_ms": 28566,
      "duration_ms": 12000,
      "text": "Devotee always likes the fame of God and not the fame of the devotee.",
      "duration_seconds": 12.0,
      "duration_bucket": "8_20s"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_ms": 44733,
      "end_ms": 54283,
      "duration_ms": 9550,
      "text": "In the same way, God likes the fame of the devotee and not His fame.",
      "duration_seconds": 9.55,
      "duration_bucket": "8_20s"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_ms": 54283,
      "end_ms": 66767,
      "duration_ms": 12484,
      "text": "God told in the Bhagavadg\u012bt\u0101 that He will be just a reflection of the devotee (Ye yath\u0101 m\u0101m\u2026).",
      "duration_seconds": 12.484,
      "duration_bucket": "8_20s"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_ms": 66766,
      "end_ms": 72648,
      "duration_ms": 5882,
      "text": "Hence, this G\u012bt\u0101 is named in your name.",
      "duration_seconds": 5.882,
      "duration_bucket": "5_8s"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_ms": 72650,
      "end_ms": 88133,
      "duration_ms": 15483,
      "text": "Like this, I have spoken the G\u012bt\u0101 in the name of some devotees like Lak\u1e63ma\u1e47ag\u012bt\u0101 and Rohitag\u012bt\u0101.",
      "duration_seconds": 15.483,
      "duration_bucket": "8_20s"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_ms": 106366,
      "end_ms": 118682,
      "duration_ms": 12316,
      "text": "If God K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a wanted to name the G\u012bt\u0101 sung by Him, He should have named it as Arjunag\u012bt\u0101.",
      "duration_seconds": 12.316,
      "duration_bucket": "8_20s"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_ms": 118683,
      "end_ms": 127367,
      "duration_ms": 8684,
      "text": "God comes down to the earth as incarnation descending from His abode",
      "duration_seconds": 8.684,
      "duration_bucket": "8_20s"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_ms": 127366,
      "end_ms": 138799,
      "duration_ms": 11433,
      "text": "bored with continuous prayers of His praise with repulsion to fame.",
      "duration_seconds": 11.433,
      "duration_bucket": "8_20s"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_ms": 154966,
      "end_ms": 165648,
      "duration_ms": 10682,
      "text": "Once God Vi\u1e63\u1e47u was also bored by praises and wanted to come down to earth as incarnation",
      "duration_seconds": 10.682,
      "duration_bucket": "8_20s"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_ms": 165650,
      "end_ms": 175600,
      "duration_ms": 9950,
      "text": "and requested all His devotees to come to earth along with Him and become enemies through scolding Him.",
      "duration_seconds": 9.95,
      "duration_bucket": "8_20s"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_ms": 175600,
      "end_ms": 188567,
      "duration_ms": 12967,
      "text": "He gave two options: - 1) To reach Him as devotee in 7 births or 2) To reach Him in 3 births as enemies.",
      "duration_seconds": 12.967,
      "duration_bucket": "8_20s"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_ms": 188600,
      "end_ms": 204933,
      "duration_ms": 16333,
      "text": "But, no devotee agreed to this. Finally, His gatekeepers Jaya and Vijaya agreed selecting the 2nd option.",
      "duration_seconds": 16.333,
      "duration_bucket": "8_20s"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_ms": 222083,
      "end_ms": 235650,
      "duration_ms": 13567,
      "text": "In the last 3rd birth, \u015ai\u015bup\u0101la pleased the Lord very much by scolding Him continuously like strong rain",
      "duration_seconds": 13.567,
      "duration_bucket": "8_20s"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_ms": 235650,
      "end_ms": 244767,
      "duration_ms": 9117,
      "text": "and the soul of \u015ai\u015bup\u0101la as a light merged in the heart of God.",
      "duration_seconds": 9.117,
      "duration_bucket": "8_20s"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_ms": 244766,
      "end_ms": 265649,
      "duration_ms": 20883,
      "text": "In the Bhagavadg\u012bt\u0101, it is told that a person, who equally enjoys both happiness and misery is called Yog\u012b (samatva\u1e43 yoga ucyate\u2026).",
      "duration_seconds": 20.883,
      "duration_bucket": "20_30s"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_ms": 282400,
      "end_ms": 291533,
      "duration_ms": 9133,
      "text": "Just like a person enjoys equally both hot and sweet dishes in meals,",
      "duration_seconds": 9.133,
      "duration_bucket": "8_20s"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_ms": 291533,
      "end_ms": 303200,
      "duration_ms": 11667,
      "text": "just like a person enjoys both pleasant and tragic scenes in seeing a cinema",
      "duration_seconds": 11.667,
      "duration_bucket": "8_20s"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_ms": 303200,
      "end_ms": 317082,
      "duration_ms": 13882,
      "text": "and just like I on entering this world as incarnation enjoy equally both happiness and misery,",
      "duration_seconds": 13.882,
      "duration_bucket": "8_20s"
    }
  ],
